1
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:21,000
You're amazing, you've all learned it!

2
00:01:22,719 --> 00:01:25,040
What's the brightest star over there?

3
00:01:25,159 --> 00:01:27,079
The Morning Star, my mom said.

4
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:30,040
Isn't the Morning Star only out in the morning?

5
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:33,400
Then what's that one?

6
00:01:33,959 --> 00:01:34,760
That one?

7
00:01:35,519 --> 00:01:36,040
Yeah.

8
00:01:36,239 --> 00:01:37,280
That one...

9
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:39,040
Should be Jupiter, I guess.

10
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,920
Ajia, do people live on the stars?

11
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,439
I don't know about that either.

12
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,879
I know.

13
00:01:50,439 --> 00:01:51,519
Dr. Meiduo's here, come quick!

14
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:52,480
Come sit with me.

15
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,959
There's a legend.

16
00:01:58,519 --> 00:02:00,560
Every star is a lamp,

17
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:03,359
lit just for those walking at night.

18
00:02:04,439 --> 00:02:05,120
Zhuoma Ajia,

19
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:07,120
what's that one that keeps blinking?

20
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:09,039
That's an airplane.

21
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,599
Does an airplane count as a star?

22
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:11,680
Sure it does.

23
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,319
It carries people,

24
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,400
and takes them where they want to go.

25
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:18,240
Can it fly to Jupiter?

26
00:02:18,919 --> 00:02:20,000
No, it can't.

27
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,039
Jupiter's too far away.

28
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,439
If you want to go there,

29
00:02:23,919 --> 00:02:24,719
you'd have to take a rocket.

30
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:27,879
I've seen a rocket on TV.

31
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:32,120
What about you? Want to ride a rocket?

32
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,000
Yes!

33
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,599
Then you have to study hard.

34
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,039
When you grow up,

35
00:02:36,319 --> 00:02:39,199
become an Astronaut, and you can ride a rocket

36
00:02:39,199 --> 00:02:40,080
to see the stars.

37
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:42,000
What's an Astronaut?

38
00:02:44,039 --> 00:02:47,280
They're the smartest

39
00:02:47,879 --> 00:02:48,879
and bravest people in the world.

40
00:02:49,879 --> 00:02:52,159
Come on, let's sing that song again.

41
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:53,280
Come on.

42
00:04:14,479 --> 00:04:15,120
Kids,

43
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,040
when our guests arrive,

44
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:16,920
let's be warm and welcoming,

45
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,199
and polite, okay?

46
00:04:18,199 --> 00:04:19,720
Okay!

47
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,879
Why aren't they here yet?

48
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:24,040
You've asked three times.

49
00:04:24,319 --> 00:04:25,680
I'm just anxious, that's all.

50
00:04:27,439 --> 00:04:29,199
Is your classmate reliable?

51
00:04:29,439 --> 00:04:30,560
You'll see in a bit.

52
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:35,600
They're here, they're here!

53
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:36,160
Line up, line up.

54
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:36,519
Come on, come on.

55
00:04:36,519 --> 00:04:37,160
Come on, come on.

56
00:04:44,079 --> 00:04:44,600
Su Qing!

57
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,399
Dr. Meiduo!

58
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,560
You finally made it.

59
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,720
How are you still so pretty?

60
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:48,439
And so slim!

61
00:04:48,519 --> 00:04:49,399
Let me introduce you.

62
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:50,680
This is Professor Fu from our institute.

63
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,879
He specializes in aerospace research.

64
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:52,360
Hello.

65
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:53,000
Hello, Dr. Meiduo.

66
00:04:53,399 --> 00:04:54,160
Hello, Professor Fu.

67
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:54,920
Hello, hello.

68
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,720
Hello, Professor Fu.

69
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:57,839
Zhang Haoran, our Village-based Official.

70
00:04:58,399 --> 00:04:58,759
Hello.

71
00:04:58,759 --> 00:04:59,319
Hello, hello.

72
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:01,079
And Zhaxi, our village guide.

73
00:05:01,279 --> 00:05:02,800
So you're the one who owes 18,000.

74
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,800
W-word's already reached you?

75
00:05:07,319 --> 00:05:08,000
Look, kids.

76
00:05:08,319 --> 00:05:09,319
What is this?

77
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,600
Sis, what is this?

78
00:05:13,879 --> 00:05:15,240
That's an astronomical telescope.

79
00:05:15,439 --> 00:05:16,319
You can see the moon with it.

80
00:05:16,959 --> 00:05:17,639
The moon!

81
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:19,000
What's on the moon?

82
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,040
There are mountains, craters,

83
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:22,519
and our Chang'e and Yutu.

84
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,519
Really?

85
00:05:24,079 --> 00:05:24,759
Go take a look.

86
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:27,759
Thank you.

87
00:05:27,759 --> 00:05:28,959
You've been such a big help.

88
00:05:28,959 --> 00:05:30,360
No need to be so polite with me.

89
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:34,800
Can you see clearly?

90
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,720
Is it clearer like this?

91
00:05:41,319 --> 00:05:42,040
In space,

92
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:44,639
you can see 16 sunrises and sunsets a day.

93
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:46,600
Because the spacecraft moves so fast,

94
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,639
in just an hour and a half,

95
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:48,959
it orbits the Earth once.

96
00:05:50,079 --> 00:05:51,680
Then when do you sleep?

97
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,480
We follow Beijing Time.

98
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,920
No matter where we fly, it's Beijing Time.

99
00:05:59,279 --> 00:06:01,680
That white band is the Milky Way.

100
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:06,240
Can you see it?

101
00:06:07,639 --> 00:06:08,199
Pretty, isn't it?

102
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:09,040
Beautiful!

103
00:06:10,399 --> 00:06:11,040
So, what do you think?

104
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:12,600
What do I think about what?

105
00:06:14,079 --> 00:06:16,120
How was the event Su Qing and I put together?

106
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:18,399
Not bad.

107
00:06:18,759 --> 00:06:19,800
Not bad?

108
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,600
You have no idea how busy Su Qing is.

109
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,839
It took me a huge effort

110
00:06:23,839 --> 00:06:24,959
to get her to come here.

111
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,079
I know, I know.

112
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,040
You just know?

113
00:06:30,519 --> 00:06:32,040
I'll have Haoran file a report right away.

114
00:06:32,639 --> 00:06:33,600
I've even thought of the title.

115
00:06:35,839 --> 00:06:37,800
"Aerospace Science Comes to the Village."

116
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,319
The kids' eyes really lit up.

117
00:06:41,639 --> 00:06:42,199
It was decent.

118
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,839
Dr. Meiduo's a great teacher.

119
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,079
It blew up! It blew up!

120
00:06:58,839 --> 00:06:59,639
What blew up?

121
00:06:59,879 --> 00:07:00,800
The Pulu orders!

122
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:01,959
Just a moment ago,

123
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,639
a fashion design company in Guangzhou

124
00:07:03,639 --> 00:07:04,439
contacted the village

125
00:07:04,439 --> 00:07:05,639
and ordered 500 pieces.

126
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,319
And the online livestream

127
00:07:07,519 --> 00:07:08,720
got dozens of orders too!

128
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,560
Is this for real?

129
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,879
Zhuoma, this is great news!

130
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,199
This is more than great news.

131
00:07:15,319 --> 00:07:16,160
This is huge!

132
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:18,839
We've got orders, we've got results.

133
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,279
So that means

134
00:07:20,279 --> 00:07:21,439
our Peach Blossom Village's

135
00:07:21,439 --> 00:07:22,879
Intangible Cultural Heritage and e-commerce project

136
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:24,160
is a success!

137
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:24,839
It's a success!

138
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,360
It's a success!

139
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:27,600
We did it!

140
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,240
Yeah!

141
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,360
We did it!

142
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,959
So how are you all gonna thank me?

143
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:31,800
Nana!

144
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,199
Nana! Nana!

145
00:07:33,199 --> 00:07:34,079
You're back.

146
00:07:38,279 --> 00:07:40,160
500 pieces, and that's just the first batch.

147
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,439
If the quality stays consistent,

148
00:07:41,759 --> 00:07:43,120
we can have a long-term partnership.

149
00:07:43,839 --> 00:07:45,920
Is everything you said really true?

150
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,120
When I went back this time,

151
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,639
I took the Pulu samples you wove

152
00:07:49,639 --> 00:07:51,120
and showed them to some designer friends.

153
00:07:51,519 --> 00:07:52,439
They absolutely loved them

154
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,399
and placed orders right on the spot.

155
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,120
Nana,

156
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,879
so this is why you went back to prep lessons?

157
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,040
What else?

158
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:01,560
Running from debt?

159
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:05,480
Nana.

160
00:08:06,079 --> 00:08:06,680
You're back.

161
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:10,560
I'm a bit tired.

162
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:11,879
I'm gonna head to my room and rest.

163
00:08:12,319 --> 00:08:12,959
Wait a second.

164
00:08:12,959 --> 00:08:13,680
I'll go help you.

165
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,639
I'll help too.

166
00:08:19,439 --> 00:08:20,800
I'm coming, I'm coming!

167
00:08:29,079 --> 00:08:30,319
Your daughter's really something.

168
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:33,679
She's better than me.

169
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,039
Of course.

170
00:08:36,279 --> 00:08:37,559
Not like her father,

171
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,039
keeping his words bottled up,

172
00:08:39,279 --> 00:08:40,360
his hand hanging in midair,

173
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,000
making others guess everything.

174
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:43,200
You...

175
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,960
Would it kill you to take some initiative?

176
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,039
I'm learning, aren't I?

177
00:08:49,919 --> 00:08:50,799
Well, from what I see,

178
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,080
you're learning pretty slowly.

179
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:05,879
Qianqian,

180
00:09:06,639 --> 00:09:07,919
We've got a lot of orders lately,

181
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:08,960
I might not be able to handle them all.

182
00:09:09,399 --> 00:09:11,240
You might have to do the livestreams later.

183
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,600
I can be your co-host.

184
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:16,120
I heard they're the ones who hype things up.

185
00:09:16,279 --> 00:09:17,600
I'll grab a big megaphone:

186
00:09:17,879 --> 00:09:19,320
Three, two, one, link's up!

187
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,399
That suits you perfectly.

188
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:21,679
Everyone's busy, huh?

189
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:22,559
Come here.

190
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,200
Look, what's this?

191
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:26,679
The district just approved it.

192
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:30,679
A policy for Peach Blossom Village's

193
00:09:30,919 --> 00:09:32,000
Intangible Cultural Heritage weaving.

194
00:09:32,159 --> 00:09:32,559
Take a look.

195
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,240
What kind of policy?

196
00:09:35,039 --> 00:09:35,840
Will they give us money?

197
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,639
Why are you always thinking about money?

198
00:09:38,039 --> 00:09:38,960
It's not just money.

199
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,159
There's also venue support.

200
00:09:40,639 --> 00:09:42,039
That old house at the village entrance,

201
00:09:42,399 --> 00:09:43,639
the district will fund its renovation.

202
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:44,519
And also,

203
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:45,960
most importantly,

204
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:47,600
brand incubation.

205
00:09:48,399 --> 00:09:49,120
The district

206
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:49,799
has included us

207
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:53,039
in their key tourism recommendation program.

208
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,000
When tourists come,

209
00:09:54,639 --> 00:09:55,960
their first stop will be our workshop.

210
00:09:57,759 --> 00:09:58,399
That's great!

211
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,559
With Peach Blossom Village's Intangible Cultural Heritage workshop,

212
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:05,120
to have all orders shipped from the workshop,

213
00:10:05,919 --> 00:10:07,080
and every single piece

214
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:09,960
will come with an official certificate.

215
00:10:10,159 --> 00:10:11,000
Teacher Nana,

216
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,039
you think so fast!

217
00:10:12,039 --> 00:10:12,919
That's a brilliant move.

218
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,200
Um, Haoran,

219
00:10:16,159 --> 00:10:17,600
if we open a workshop,

220
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,240
do we have to hire people?

221
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:21,840
And we'll have to use machines, right?

222
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,279
I know what you're worried about.

223
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:25,440
Come take a look.

224
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,159
This document mentions

225
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,679
"protective development."

226
00:10:30,039 --> 00:10:30,440
And here,

227
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,039
"its core processes

228
00:10:32,039 --> 00:10:33,919
must remain purely handmade."

229
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:35,840
We're building this workshop

230
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,879
not to let machines replace your hands,

231
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,960
but so more young people

232
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:40,799
have a place to sit down

233
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:42,200
and learn this craft from you.

234
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:44,480
Well,

235
00:10:44,879 --> 00:10:47,480
can this workshop really teach everyone?

236
00:10:48,039 --> 00:10:49,120
As long as you're willing to teach,

237
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:50,679
I promise we'll keep it running.

238
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,600
We're not just doing this to sell goods.

239
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,320
We want to turn this craft

240
00:10:54,559 --> 00:10:56,240
into a signature of Peach Blossom Village

241
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,720
and pass it down, right?

242
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,480
Then from now on,

243
00:11:02,919 --> 00:11:04,240
I won't call you Sister Zhuoma anymore.

244
00:11:04,879 --> 00:11:05,679
I'll call you...

245
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,120
Teacher Zhuoma!

246
00:11:08,039 --> 00:11:08,799
Yes, yes, yes!

247
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:10,600
Teacher Zhuoma!

248
00:11:10,799 --> 00:11:12,000
Teacher Nana!

249
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,919
Teacher Haoran!

250
00:11:13,919 --> 00:11:15,320
Teacher Qianqian!

251
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,720
To think someone would call me teacher one day!

252
00:11:21,679 --> 00:11:24,240
Congrats on our Intangible Cultural Heritage workshop's launch!

253
00:12:06,399 --> 00:12:07,080
Teacher Zhuoma,

254
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:08,960
When will this batch of yarn be ready?

255
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,519
Everyone's waiting to get on the looms.

256
00:12:10,799 --> 00:12:11,440
Soon, soon.

257
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:13,559
Zhuoma! Zhuoma!

258
00:12:13,879 --> 00:12:14,679
Come take a look!

259
00:12:14,919 --> 00:12:16,399
Something's wrong with this batch of yarn.

260
00:12:16,399 --> 00:12:17,440
It's all Uneven dyeing.

261
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,639
Why won't this yarn take the dye?
